This paper proposes a neural cross-lingual coreference model that uses multi-lingual embeddings and language-independent features. The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks such as entity linking and coreference resolution, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural networks and machine learning algorithms also suggests that the paper could be relevant to sub-categories such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and natural language processing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its model using extrinsic evaluation, which involves entity linking accuracy, suggesting that it could also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
